## Rainbow deployments - parallel variant rollout
direction: down

intro: {
  shape: text
  label: "Deploying agent changes (new prompt, new model, new tools) is RISKY.\nQuality is hard to measure pre-deployment; users notice changes.\n\nRainbow deployment: run K variants IN PRODUCTION, each on a slice of traffic.\nCollect per-variant metrics. Promote the winner; roll back the rest."
  style.italic: true
  style.font-color: "#7c3aed"
}

oldway: {
  label: "BIG BANG (risky)"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fee2e2"
  style.stroke: "#dc2626"
  body: {label: "Deploy new prompt / model / tools to 100% of traffic.\nIf it's worse, you find out from user complaints.\nRollback takes hours; damage is done."; shape: text}
}

rainbow: {
  label: "RAINBOW (parallel variants)"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#bbf7d0"
  style.stroke: "#16a34a"
  body: {label: "Variant A (control): 70% of traffic, current prompt + Sonnet\nVariant B: 10% of traffic, new prompt + Sonnet\nVariant C: 10% of traffic, current prompt + new Sonnet version\nVariant D: 10% of traffic, new prompt + new model\n\nPer-variant metrics:\n  Cost / query\n  Latency p50, p95\n  Eval score\n  User feedback\n  Error rate"; shape: text}
}

decisions: {
  label: "Decision flow"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fde68a"
  style.stroke: "#d97706"
  body: {label: "Daily: review per-variant metrics.\nA variant wins -> promote (shift traffic).\nA variant fails -> roll back (drop traffic to 0).\nA variant ties -> keep running until significance.\n\nLike feature flags + experimentation,\nadapted to LLM-specific axes (model, prompt, tools)."; shape: text}
}

intro -> oldway
intro -> rainbow
oldway -> decisions: "vs"
rainbow -> decisions
